🟦 Use Case: The Environmental & Safety Audit

AI in legal work must be inspected before it is trusted.

That is why LCES includes a Hallucination Guard inside the Environmental & Safety Audit.

🔹 Hallucination Guard

The AI is prompted to adopt the Inspector role.

Its job is not to create unchecked authority.

Its job is to flag risk.

The Inspector must acknowledge that every AI-generated citation requires manual verification by:

- 🧩 Architect — structural and procedural review

• 👤 Human — final judgment and responsibility

🛡️ The safety principle:

No citation should be trusted merely because it sounds legal.

No rule should be accepted merely because it looks formatted.

No authority should enter the record without verification.

🟨 LCES uses AI under constraint

The goal is not blind automation.

The goal is:

- Reduce drift

• Expose weakness

• Flag uncertainty

• Preserve accountability

• Keep humans in control

⚖️ AI may assist the workflow.

But the record belongs to the human decision-maker.

